274
00:15:56.976 --> 00:16:00.696
that if we co-treat with an inhibitor of ferroptosis

275
00:16:00.796 --> 00:16:02.176
called ferrostatin 1,

276
00:16:03.036 --> 00:16:03.556
that this

277
00:16:04.656 --> 00:16:08.516
could suppress the phenotype. And so he did this

278
00:16:09.076 --> 00:16:12.376
in a little bit different cell line, which now

279
00:16:12.896 --> 00:16:16.756
not only is NEAT1 deficient, but it's only deficient

280
00:16:16.936 --> 00:16:20.926
for the longer isoform of NEAT1, which is the

281
00:16:21.016 --> 00:16:23.356
one that scaffolds paraspeckles,

282
00:16:24.456 --> 00:16:27.856
and the shorter polyadenylated isoform is left

283
00:16:27.896 --> 00:16:28.536
intact.

284
00:16:29.636 --> 00:16:31.856
And indeed, so when Decari

285
00:16:33.556 --> 00:16:37.476
treated these cells lacking paraspeckle isoform, shown

286
00:16:37.536 --> 00:16:40.336
in red here, they are sensitive and

287
00:16:40.956 --> 00:16:43.936
ferrostatin was able to at least partially

288
00:16:44.036 --> 00:16:47.846
reverse the sensitivity. So this told us that

289
00:16:49.156 --> 00:16:52.776
the paraspeckle form of NEAT1

290
00:16:52.786 --> 00:16:53.636
is

291
00:16:54.576 --> 00:16:55.726
critical for

292
00:16:58.536 --> 00:17:01.316
protecting cells from ferroptosis.

293
00:17:03.636 --> 00:17:07.497
So this was all done, as I mentioned, in a myeloid leukemia

294
00:17:07.636 --> 00:17:10.956
cell for technical reasons. So the next question is

295
00:17:11.017 --> 00:17:14.656
whether, going back now to the PDAC models,

296
00:17:14.936 --> 00:17:17.686
do these observations hold?

297
00:17:18.676 --> 00:17:21.576
And so looking again at

298
00:17:22.456 --> 00:17:23.477
the paraspeckle

299
00:17:25.737 --> 00:17:29.446
prevalence within classical versus basal, there's a

300
00:17:29.496 --> 00:17:32.476
clear reduction in paraspeckle levels

301
00:17:32.996 --> 00:17:34.896
in the basal-like cells.

302
00:17:36.636 --> 00:17:37.336
And in fact,

303
00:17:38.876 --> 00:17:42.316
if you just treat these cells with RSL3

304
00:17:43.176 --> 00:17:47.036
straight up, the basal-like cells are indeed more sensitive

305
00:17:47.116 --> 00:17:48.056
to these drugs.

306
00:17:50.256 --> 00:17:50.516
So,

307
00:17:53.056 --> 00:17:56.656
Decari next wanted to see if he can modulate the

308
00:17:56.716 --> 00:18:00.056
levels of paraspeckles through controlling the

309
00:18:00.116 --> 00:18:03.516
expression of NEAT1. And so he did this using a

310
00:18:03.576 --> 00:18:06.816
CRISPR system, CRISPRi, which can

311
00:18:06.876 --> 00:18:10.556
transcriptionally repressNEAT1, and this works

312
00:18:10.956 --> 00:18:14.576
very, very well. They become undetectable in these

313
00:18:16.876 --> 00:18:18.446
guide RNA-treated cells.

314
00:18:19.776 --> 00:18:21.916
And in fact, just by

315
00:18:23.076 --> 00:18:24.396
depleting NEAT1,

316
00:18:25.576 --> 00:18:29.076
Dikari could see that the gene expression

317
00:18:29.476 --> 00:18:33.116
score, that PAMG score, shifts to a more

318
00:18:33.136 --> 00:18:33.956
basal-like

319
00:18:34.776 --> 00:18:35.876
expression pattern.

320
00:18:37.456 --> 00:18:40.576
And then when he treated these cells,

321
00:18:41.176 --> 00:18:43.096
several different cell lines,

322
00:18:44.536 --> 00:18:48.056
both with NEAT1 knockdown and

323
00:18:48.556 --> 00:18:51.276
then applied the GPX4 inhibitor,

324
00:18:52.196 --> 00:18:55.156
we can see that indeed the loss of NEAT1

325
00:18:55.336 --> 00:18:56.716
sensitizes these

326
00:18:58.016 --> 00:18:59.056
cells to

327
00:19:00.256 --> 00:19:00.916
the drug.

328
00:19:01.936 --> 00:19:05.876
So next he asked, "Can we go the opposite direction?" So if we

329
00:19:05.976 --> 00:19:06.276
take

330
00:19:07.456 --> 00:19:11.206
MiaPaCa cells, which are more basal-like cells, and

331
00:19:11.276 --> 00:19:14.976
now use CRISPRa to activate the

332
00:19:15.016 --> 00:19:18.676
expression transcriptionally of NEAT1, what

333
00:19:18.796 --> 00:19:22.296
happens? And so the first thing is that we can

334
00:19:22.376 --> 00:19:22.956
indeed

335
00:19:24.276 --> 00:19:27.456
increase these NEAT1 paraspeckle

336
00:19:28.096 --> 00:19:29.996
using CRISPRa.

337
00:19:32.196 --> 00:19:33.236
And so we get a

338
00:19:34.156 --> 00:19:36.656
higher number of paraspeckles in these cells.

339
00:19:37.356 --> 00:19:39.976
And then what happens if we treat with the drugs?

340
00:19:41.216 --> 00:19:41.476
So,

341
00:19:42.736 --> 00:19:46.716
in these cells now, these are now basal-type cells,

342
00:19:46.816 --> 00:19:50.636
which we've boosted the paraspeckle levels

343
00:19:50.816 --> 00:19:54.336
in them. And indeed, there's a slight but significant

344
00:19:54.676 --> 00:19:57.696
increase in their resistance to the

345
00:19:57.756 --> 00:19:59.656
ferroptosis-inducing drugs.

346
00:20:01.136 --> 00:20:05.116
So this told us then that NEAT1 induction is sufficient

347
00:20:05.196 --> 00:20:08.876
to increase the resistance to these inhibitors in PDAC

348
00:20:08.976 --> 00:20:09.356
cells.

349
00:20:11.236 --> 00:20:15.016
So Dikari went on to do further work, which I don't

350
00:20:15.076 --> 00:20:18.976
have time to go into great detail about, but he was

351
00:20:19.076 --> 00:20:23.006
able to find an RNA-binding protein called

352
00:20:23.116 --> 00:20:23.646
quaking,

353
00:20:25.616 --> 00:20:28.696
which is involved in the biogenesis of

354
00:20:29.256 --> 00:20:29.816
NEAT1.

355
00:20:31.216 --> 00:20:31.396
So

356
00:20:33.236 --> 00:20:36.456
