385
00:22:18.636 --> 00:22:22.445
So paraspeckles, we know then from this

386
00:22:22.496 --> 00:22:25.235
work that they suppress

387
00:22:26.076 --> 00:22:29.976
oxidative stress pathways. So now the question becomes:

388
00:22:30.016 --> 00:22:33.556
What are they actually doing to gene expression and

389
00:22:33.616 --> 00:22:34.316
splicing?

390
00:22:35.156 --> 00:22:37.216
And so I want to come back

391
00:22:38.556 --> 00:22:41.616
to the beginning of this talk where

392
00:22:42.376 --> 00:22:44.996
I was talking about retained introns.

393
00:22:45.976 --> 00:22:46.206
And

394
00:22:47.456 --> 00:22:51.276
so we started to think about another collaboration that we did

395
00:22:51.316 --> 00:22:53.456
with Suzanne Walker's group at Harvard,

396
00:22:55.016 --> 00:22:58.976
where we found that if you treat with inhibitors

397
00:22:59.156 --> 00:23:02.536
of this enzyme called OGT, this is a

398
00:23:02.556 --> 00:23:06.156
glycosyltransferase. It puts this O-linked glucanac

399
00:23:06.276 --> 00:23:09.606
molecule onto serine and threonine residues,

400
00:23:10.156 --> 00:23:11.796
and this is really

401
00:23:12.736 --> 00:23:16.056
mutually exclusive with many kinases that would

402
00:23:16.096 --> 00:23:18.056
phosphorylate the same residues.

403
00:23:19.036 --> 00:23:22.776
So if you treat with an inhibitor of this drug, prevent

404
00:23:22.856 --> 00:23:26.376
glucanac, this upregulates phosphoproteins,

405
00:23:26.756 --> 00:23:29.056
specifically in many splicing factors.

406
00:23:31.476 --> 00:23:35.096
And if we look now at splicing

407
00:23:35.156 --> 00:23:38.876
levels, we see this really striking specificity where

408
00:23:39.436 --> 00:23:42.976
we essentially lose retained introns when we

409
00:23:43.016 --> 00:23:44.796
inhibit OGT,

410
00:23:45.956 --> 00:23:49.436
and other splicing events are relatively unaffected.

411
00:23:50.016 --> 00:23:53.836
We could drive this in the opposite direction using an

412
00:23:53.916 --> 00:23:57.336
OGA inhibitor. So preventing the removal of

413
00:23:57.376 --> 00:24:00.656
glucanac increases glucanac modifications.

414
00:24:01.716 --> 00:24:05.416
And so we asked next whether in

415
00:24:05.496 --> 00:24:08.116
these pancreatic cancer cell

416
00:24:08.176 --> 00:24:11.976
linesWhat happens if we treat with these

417
00:24:12.076 --> 00:24:15.436
modulators of OGA or OGT? And in fact,

418
00:24:15.536 --> 00:24:19.166
particularly when we increase the

419
00:24:19.166 --> 00:24:19.936
GluCNAC

420
00:24:20.876 --> 00:24:24.076
levels in these cells, we see a strong

421
00:24:24.296 --> 00:24:27.235
increase in the level of paraspeckles.

422
00:24:27.836 --> 00:24:31.716
And many of these paraspeckle-associated proteins

423
00:24:31.796 --> 00:24:35.056
are known to be modified by OGT.

424
00:24:35.936 --> 00:24:37.546
And so we think that

425
00:24:38.696 --> 00:24:42.176
this is kind of our working model, is

426
00:24:42.236 --> 00:24:45.496
that these nuclear bodies sort of

427
00:24:45.816 --> 00:24:48.156
coexist and that

428
00:24:48.876 --> 00:24:52.396
paraspeckles are really defined and probably

429
00:24:52.456 --> 00:24:55.496
placed in distinct nuclear

430
00:24:55.636 --> 00:24:58.556
chromatin neighborhoods or

431
00:24:58.616 --> 00:25:02.376
individual loci through modifications of

432
00:25:02.436 --> 00:25:06.256
histones and associated splicing

433
00:25:06.396 --> 00:25:09.936
factors in those bodies may be predominantly

434
00:25:09.976 --> 00:25:13.236
GluCNAC modified, resulting in splicing inhibition,

435
00:25:13.896 --> 00:25:17.436
retention of those intron-containing isoforms

436
00:25:17.536 --> 00:25:18.696
within these bodies.

437
00:25:19.796 --> 00:25:23.356
Whereas nuclear speckles are driven by

438
00:25:23.396 --> 00:25:27.236
phosphorylation, have high splicing activity and

439
00:25:27.296 --> 00:25:28.876
high export activity.

440
00:25:30.916 --> 00:25:34.076
So, I just want to thank you all for being here

