486
00:28:14.676 --> 00:28:14.896
So

487
00:28:17.096 --> 00:28:18.176
in many cases,

488
00:28:19.016 --> 00:28:22.886
the detained intron isoform will only form

489
00:28:23.216 --> 00:28:26.396
if the splice variant that would result in

490
00:28:26.435 --> 00:28:29.385
nonsense-mediated decay is chosen.

491
00:28:30.296 --> 00:28:31.076
So in other words,

492
00:28:32.496 --> 00:28:33.256
even if those

493
00:28:34.296 --> 00:28:38.176
detained introns are spliced, it creates a

494
00:28:38.616 --> 00:28:40.726
transcript that will then undergo decay.

495
00:28:41.336 --> 00:28:44.996
So in some cases, it really represents a

496
00:28:45.096 --> 00:28:48.616
negative gene expression regulatory pathway.

497
00:28:50.056 --> 00:28:50.596
Thank you very much.

498
00:28:50.856 --> 00:28:50.866
Thank you.

