00:57:16.608 --> 00:57:20.268
regions, which are really important in RNA localization, propensity for

984
00:57:20.288 --> 00:57:22.198
translation, and stability of the

985
00:57:22.228 --> 00:57:25.848
transcript. So as a hematologist, I became

986
00:57:25.948 --> 00:57:29.888
interested in the topic of splicing right when I started my lab about 12 years ago,

